CatDescriptText: Mr. William Washington, maintenance man, Fifth ward, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in the Pittsburgh Courier Newspaper, January 6, 1962, pg.7 with question: "What goal or goals should the Pittsburgh Negro aim for in 1962?" answer reads: "He should strive to be 100 per cent American like the rest."
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Portrait of young man wearing light colored fedora with dark band, diagonally striped tie, and light colored overcoat with upturned collar standing in front of Jenkins Arcade, Liberty Avenue, Downtown; Portrait of William Washington wearing light colored fedora with dark band, standing in front of Jenkins Arcade, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
